Political bigwigs eyeing presidency in 2022 are jostling for president Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s populous Mt. Kenya voting bloc despite perceived division in the region. &hellip;today, it was the turn of ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi to visit the area and try to woo residents to back his candidature. Mudavadi has in recent times visited the region three times in a bid to make inroads in president Kenyatta&rsquo;s backyard. And as Daniel Kariuki reports, leaders from the region are strategically positioning themselves as regional kingpins in order to have a say in the coming elections.
